picoctf Binary Gauntlet 1 writeup

1.use "checksec --file=gauntlet" to look its defence , we can know that it doesnt open NX

2.we use ghidra to decompiler it and we can see it fget our first input and store in a 1000 big heap (local_10) 

3.then it printf it our , fget our input again but this time it strcpy input in 104 big string in stack (local_78)

4.so we can write a shellcode on local_10 and it will copy on local_78 which we can know its address at the first

5.now we need to calculate its offset (how far does local_78 to return address on stack)

  40068f:       89 7d 8c                mov    DWORD PTR [rbp-0x74],edi

6.we can know offset equal 0x74 + 0x8 (saved_rbp) and then is return address

7.so payload should be shellcode + b"a"*offset + p64(local_78_addr)

=> write shellcode on stack 
=> overlap remaining space
=> use our shellcode address to overlap the return address

8.write a python script (binary_gauntlet1.py)

9.get flag!

